text: Horacio White (April 2, 1927 - August 26, 2017) was an Argentine swimmer. He was born in Buenos Aires. He competed at the 1948 Summer Olympics in the 100 m freestyle and 4Ã—200 m freestyle relay, reaching the final in the latter and coming 6th.
